          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781784756253" href="/book/show/36114391-then-she-was-gone">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32081931-lisa?shelf=thrillers">thrillers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2665508698" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12248544359258938436">Ellie Mack went missing when she was 15 years of age the youngest of three children she left her house to go to the library &amp; was never seen again, Ten years later her mother Laurel is finding it hard to adjust after Ellies disappearance, she feels hopeless &amp; her world just stopped.<br/><br/><br/>Its not until she meets Floyd Dunn she has finally found happiness or has she? Paul her husband has moved on so does Laurel Floyd introduces his daughter Poppy &amp; S J to her , Laurel is very close to Poppy she looks li</span>
  <span id="freeText12248544359258938436" style="display:none">Ellie Mack went missing when she was 15 years of age the youngest of three children she left her house to go to the library &amp; was never seen again, Ten years later her mother Laurel is finding it hard to adjust after Ellies disappearance, she feels hopeless &amp; her world just stopped.<br /><br /><br />Its not until she meets Floyd Dunn she has finally found happiness or has she? Paul her husband has moved on so does Laurel Floyd introduces his daughter Poppy &amp; S J to her , Laurel is very close to Poppy she looks like her daughter Ellie Poppy is very smart Laurel becomes very close to her.<br /><br /><br />Its not until the relationship between Floyd &amp; Laurel escalate that secrets &amp; Lies are revealed the prose goes from then to now their is a diary of the truths to be told.<br />Will Laurel find her Ellie or is Floyd the man he says he is?<br /><br /><br />MY THOUGHTS<br />I loved every minute of this dark disturbing thriller, once again miss Jewell has written another gem that tantalises the readers appetite this is gritty twisty &amp; delicious to read I want more.</span>
