<div id="review_3788104466" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3788104466" />
    <a title="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25532045-kat-books-are-comfort-food"><img alt="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617935580p2/25532045.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3788104466?book_show_action=true">Jul 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" href="/user/show/25532045-kat-books-are-comfort-food">Kat (Books are Comfort Food)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/36012399-then-she-was-gone">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25532045-kat-books-are-comfort-food?shelf=2021-books">2021-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3788104466" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6228216506854157845">This is a slow-burn mystery and family drama. It’s about families and adjustments after the unthinkable happens. Fifteen year old Ellie Mack disappears without a trace. There is pain, but remarkable strength. There is deception and there is honesty. The book is written in parts, outlining different periods in the story. There is also a big surprise in the story and I didn’t see it coming. There are some twists and turns, some I did see coming. <br/><br/>Normally, I don’t like slow burn mysteries, but I di</span>
  <span id="freeText6228216506854157845" style="display:none">This is a slow-burn mystery and family drama. It’s about families and adjustments after the unthinkable happens. Fifteen year old Ellie Mack disappears without a trace. There is pain, but remarkable strength. There is deception and there is honesty. The book is written in parts, outlining different periods in the story. There is also a big surprise in the story and I didn’t see it coming. There are some twists and turns, some I did see coming. <br /><br />Normally, I don’t like slow burn mysteries, but I did enjoy this one because of the characters. The characters were fleshed out beautifully and I felt their pain and triumphs. <br /><br />There were a couple issues that seemed implausible to me, but I got caught up in the story and went with the flow. I very much enjoyed he book. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6228216506854157845" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


